Energy Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi as introduced some community members in Cape Town to green energy alternatives such as biofuel and solar energy. CAPE TOWN - Energy Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi says South Africans should make use of alternative energy sources. Kubayi was in Cape Town on Tuesday. She introduced some community members to green energy alternatives such as biofuel and solar energy. The minister says government is busy with an electrification project in some areas. We ve received good feedback in terms of the project but there s still a lot of work to be done that involves connecting the community. #EnergySafety Energy Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi engaging the Joe Slovo community on the safe usage of electricity and alternative energy. KB pic.twitter.com/nzVp9gREYD(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)